ns held by grebow include deputy president of sony electronics inc president of sony’s broadcast and professional company president and chief executive officer of chyron corporation executive vice president at cbs inc reporting to chairman laurence tisch vice president at jp morgan  co inc president of jp morgan lease funding corp chief operating officer and evp of the bowery savings bank contents  career  current trustee and board positions  education  awards  references careeredit edward grebow began his career at morgan guaranty trust company as an accountant in  he was named executive vice president and coo of bowery savings bank  in this role mr grebow worked with investors including richard ravitch warren buffett and laurence tisch to develop an acquisition plan for the troubled bank  after the implementation of several costsaving measures that returned the bank to profitability bowery was sold to hf ahmanson  co for  million in   in  mr grebow became executive vice president of cbs inc where he oversaw the purchase and renovation of the historic ed sullivan theater as a home for late show with david letterman purchased for  million initial work at the building revealed challenges that many industry insiders doubted he could overcome but the project was completed in  weeks upon completion the cbsowned theater and adjacent building boasted stateoftheart production and office spaces that also became home to the new york city mayors office of film theatre  broadcasting in  mr grebow was named president of teletv systems a joint venture between three regional telephone companies that were attempting to develop interactive television services in this role he testified before the federal communications commission on issues surrounding advanced television systems and the allotment of spectrum for digital television broadcasting following this position mr grebow joined chyron corporation a leading television production equipment maker as president and saw this entity through a period of prosperity in  beginning in  mr grebow led sony broadcast and professional company through the broadcasting industrys transition from traditional to digital technology and oversaw the companys partnership with panavision inc to bring highquality digital cameras to leading filmmakers around the world after the tragedy of september   mr grebow stepped down from his role at sony when he was asked to head the metropolitan television alliance the organization of new york city broadcasters that was responsible for replacing the broadcast and emergency services transmission facilities that were destroyed in the attack mr grebow worked to organize alternative means of broadcasting while a permanent site for a new tower was found and constructed after consideration of locations in new jersey and on governors island in new york harbor mr grebow signed an agreement in  to install  analog and digital antennas on the new freedom tower at the world trade center site in  mr grebow joined ullico a washington dcbased labor unionaffiliated financial services and insurance company as president dealing with fallout from several years of financial abuses and criminal activity by former executives and directors he organized an infusion of capital sold the companys headquarters and led a management overhaul that restored the companys financial strength and reputation in a short time his work at ullico earned him distinction as a turnaround specialist for financial services and laborfocused companies following this success mr grebow joined the private equity firm jc flowers  co as managing director in  and was retained to oversee a transaction that attempted to privatize student loan giant sallie mae unionowned amalgamated bank was suffering from deficits that resulted from failed real estate loans and was under threat of closure by the fdic when mr grebow was hired as president and ceo in  he was able to raise  million in capital for the bank from billionaire investors wilbur ross and ron burkle and oversaw the development of innovative retail banking products under mr grebows leadership amalgamated served as the bank of the democratic national committee the presidential inaugural committee of  and the unofficial financial institution of the occupy wall street movement on several occasions throughout mr grebows tenure amalgamated brought derivative lawsuits against corporations on behalf of its many pension fund clients securing its reputation as a bank that would stand against corporate wrongdoing with amalgamated banks stability restored in  mr grebow returned to investment banking as managing director of triartisan capital partners current trustee and board positionsedit grebow serves on the board of directors for diamond offshore drilling inc where he is a director and the chairman of the audit committee in addition he serves as a trustee of thirteenwnet of the laborers international union charitable foundation and serves on the board of the international association of fire fighters foundation in march  grebow joined the alcentra capital corporation board as an independent director in september  grebow joined the xenith bankhares board as the anchorage capital groups representative grebow’s past board positions include the george washington university american film institute theatre development fund panavision inc educationedit grebow graduated from the george washington university school of business awardsedit in  the emerald isle society awarded grebow the robert briscoe award which is given annually to members of new york’s jewish community in recognition of their efforts to better the lives of irish immigrants referencesedit  birnbaum birnbaum  may  sallie mae forced out ceo say sources washington post retrieved  august    edward grebow to leave sony to lead effort to find site for new york tv tower digital content producer retrieved  august    labor insurer ullico names acting president retrieved  august    a b business